> =20
> Kia ora, Zach and the Privacy Team, Thank you for sharing the material =
to date. I=E2=80=99ve reviewed the documents and can see that several =
items appear to be missing. Could you please provide the following =
additional information and records: Correspondence
> =20
> =20
> Kia ora, Zach and the Privacy Team,
> =20
> Thank you for sharing the material to date. I=E2=80=99ve reviewed the =
documents and can see that several items appear to be missing. Could you =
please provide the following additional information and records:
> =20
> Correspondence and communications
> (Note: The timestamps referenced below appear to follow a non-NZT time =
zone (likely UTC). Please adjust your searches accordingly.)
> =20
> The email from Stephen Walker (ASUR NZ Consultant) to Grant Metson, =
referred to in the email sent by Grant Metson  to himself dated 12 =
August 2025 at 04:59.
> The correspondence referred to in the email between Lei Yu and Grant =
on or around Sunday, 17 August 2025, as mentioned again in the email of =
Monday, 18 August 2025 at 20:59.
> Any phone conversations between Grant Metson and Lei Yu (ASUR NZ, =
Building Consultant, +64 21 467 094) on or around Sunday, 17 August =
2025.
> Any calls between Grant Metson and Lei Yu (ASUR NZ) on or after =
Thursday, 21 August 2025.
> As referenced in the email from Grant to Stephen Walker dated 16 =
September 2025 at 3:07 am, details or recordings of the call between =
Grant and Stephen that occurred earlier that day or the day prior.
> =20
> Internal and external communications referencing my claim
> =20
> Any emails, chats, text, transcripts or notes in your systems that =
contain C90306048.
> Any emails, chats, text,  transcripts or notes in your systems that =
contain =E2=80=9C23 Mays=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9C23 Mays Road=E2=80=9D.
> Any emails, texts, or chat messages to or from the following addresses =
or individuals that reference claim C90306048, my propert (=E2=80=9C23 =
Mays=E2=80=9D)  or myself (under any name variation, as I see often =
misspelled):
> Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz <mailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>
> Bryan.Strong@tower.co.nz <mailto:Bryan.Strong@tower.co.nz>
> Megan.Jensen@tower.co.nz <mailto:Megan.Jensen@tower.co.nz>
> Kelly.Mason@tower.co.nz <mailto:Kelly.Mason@tower.co.nz>
> Chris.Cornwall@tower.co.nz <mailto:Chris.Cornwall@tower.co.nz>
> Zach.Pion@tower.co.nz <mailto:Zach.Pion@tower.co.nz>
> Sasha.Cotterill@tower.co.nz <mailto:Sasha.Cotterill@tower.co.nz>
> and any other person copied or involved in communications related to =
the claim.
> Any internal emails or external communications (including subject =
lines, message text, or attachment names) that include the text =
=E2=80=9CC90306048=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9C23 Mays Road=E2=80=9D / =E2=80=9C2=
3 Mays=E2=80=9D.
> Any internal communications (texts, chats, or call notes) concerning =
the claim, the property, or myself.
> Any phone transcripts that include =E2=80=9CC90306048=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C=
23 Mays Road=E2=80=9D, or =E2=80=9C23 Mays=E2=80=9D.
> =20
> =20
> Notification of privacy breach
> =20
> I would also like to formally notify a potential privacy breach.
> On 10 August 2025, Grant Metson shared my name and mobile number with =
Stephen Walker (ASUR NZ) by email without my consent and without a clear =
business reason. Given that I have since raised concerns about Mr =
Walker=E2=80=99s independence, I believe this disclosure was =
inappropriate and may present a risk to my privacy and safety.
> =20
> Please confirm that this incident will be logged and investigated in =
accordance with Tower=E2=80=99s privacy obligations and the Privacy Act =
2020.
> =20
> Please confirm receipt of this email and advise when I can expect a =
response or update on both the information request and the privacy =
breach notification.
> =20
> Ng=C4=81 mihi,
> Raffaella
> =20
